CRYPTOGRAPHIC PROVENANCE
  The frozen scientific record — every pre-registration spec and SHA-256
  manifest, the authored corpora, the offline knowledge fixture, and the
  manuscripts for LISM, LMD, the four cohorts (yeast 4825 / GitHub 992 /
  knowledge 793 / digital swarm), the three validation stages, the Hinton and
  Russell tests, and the benchmark-governance suite — is fingerprinted into a
  single Merkle root in PROVENANCE.lock.json.

  Reproduce freely; that is the point. But a faithful reproduction recomputes
  the same root, which is the cryptographic reference back to this source. Run:

      python3 provenance/verify_provenance.py

  You MAY reproduce, extend, and build upon this work (including its NULL and
  NEGATIVE results). You MUST retain this attribution and cite the origin. You
  may NOT present this work, or a reproduction of it, as your own origin.

  Provenance proves integrity, priority (first-publication), and attribution.
  It does not — and cannot — prevent copying; it makes misattribution
  detectable and gives the originator a dated, checkable record. For public,
  reproducible work this is the correct protection: signatures + content hashes,
  not encryption.

